-- Chicago Bulls Beat 76ers 103-91 in Opening Game of NBA Playoffs
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-04-28T19:49:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/chicago-bulls-beat-76ers-103-91-in-opening-game-of-nba-playoffs.html
The Chicago Bulls defeated the
Philadelphia 76ers 103-91 in the opening game of the National
Basketball Association playoffs.  Derrick Rose  had 23 points, nine rebounds and nine assists
to lead Chicago, the No. 1 seed in the Eastern Conference, to
the home win. Elton Brand scored 19 points for No. 8
Philadelphia.  Chicago hosts Game 2 in the best-of-seven series on May 1.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  